Source: univention-windows-installer
Section: univention
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Univention GmbH <packages@univention.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0), univention-config-dev, unzip, patch
Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: univention-windows-installer
Architecture: all
Depends: univention-client-boot-pxe, syslinux | syslinux-bin, univention-config-registry, univention-samba, lynx, unzip, univention-windows-installer-image-linux, univention-directory-listener
Description: UCS - unattended Windows installation
 The Univention Windows Installer integrates Microsoft's
 unattended installation into UCS. Windows computers can
 be scheduled to be installed using Univention Admin, and
 will then be installed without manual intervention.
 .
 This package is part of Univention Corporate Server (UCS),
 an integrated, directory driven solution for managing
 corporate environments. For more information about UCS,
 refer to: http://www.univention.de/

Package: univention-windows-installer-image-linux
Architecture: any 
Depends: lynx, unzip, python2.4, univention-config-registry
Conflicts: univention-windows-installer (<< 1.2-1)
Description: Customized Linux-based Windows installation image
 This package downloads a Linux-image from the unattended-website,
 and adjusts the autoexec.bat to the hostname this packages is
 installed on.
 .
 This package is part of Univention Corporate Server (UCS),
 an integrated, directory driven solution for managing
 corporate environments. For more information about UCS,
 refer to: http://www.univention.de/

